good for a fun read this text provides an interesting overall account of oddities that happened during one of the greatest conflicts of all time . there are some factual data within the book that well-versed readers have identified that could possibly be considered in a later edition . for these individuals , there are countless multi-volume and 500+ page accounts of the history of world war ii . however , to a novice , this work provides short , readable sections about interesting and less known aspects of the second world war . this book makes one reflect on the strange little things that can alter the course of human history . if nothing else , it raises your curiosity to read more works on the topic or the issue or story that you are most interested in . after all , is n't that what reading and exploring information is all about